title: Kotlin compile daemon
body:
First variant of compile daemon with the following properties

- disabled by default
- enabled in idea/jps by adding -Dkotlin.daemon.enabled to  Settings -> Build, Execution, Deployment -> Compiler -> User-local build process VM options
- runs on the first compilation
- stops with any exiting idea (with updated kotlin plugin) 
- could be stopped manually with main class org.jetbrains.kotlin.rmi.kotlinr.KotlinCompilerClient (part of kotlin-compiler.jar) and argument --stop-daemon
- daemon logs to log file \<temp folder\>/kotlin-daemon.\<ts\>.log
- checks if loaded with proper version of a compiler (by comparing classpath and md5 of files in it) and if it doesn't match - restarts the daemon with desired compiler

title: KT-8708 Function to strip leading whitespaces
body:
Function to strip leading whitespace characters before the specified delimiter character (pipe by default). Intended to be partial solution of [KT-6620 Indent safe """ syntax](https://youtrack.jetbrains.com/issue/KT-6620)

`trimMargin` is very similar to `stripMargin` in Scala and Groovy so we can think it is a common solution.

`trimMargin` is works slightly different than `stripMarign` in Scala and Groovy. The main difference is that by default `trimMargin` removes only whitespaces on the contrary `stripMargin` removes all control characters that I believe is wrong. 

However if user really need exact the same behaviour he always can specify custom `whitespacePredicate` like this:

```kotlin
trimMargin { it <= ' ' }
```

title: get rid of deprecated method usage
KT-4844 Support asReversed() for lists
body:
Introduces `asReversed` extension function. The main difference over `reverse` is that it only creates a view of the original `List`. There are two implementations of it: for `List<T>` and for `MutableList<T>`. In mutable version we also can modify a view returned by `asReversed` and all changes will be reflected in the original list. We also can chain `asReversed` and `subList` and it will still work.

The only thing doesn't work is mutable sublist in JavaScript: our own sub-list implementation doesn't support it yet so it doesn't work with reversed lists too. This is why corresponding test is extracted to JVM only version

title: Maven: take logger every time
body:
The root cause of problem is that we take logger at too early stage so there is initial bootstrap maven logger that is replaced by plexus container via injector at later initialization stage. We have to use injected logger rather than initial bootstrap logger. At the same time there is no actual performance advantage to have LOG field because of JIT inliner will inline getLog() body anyway.

The commits were cherrypicked from other branches that may eventually land on master too.

title: Make $metadata$ a non-enumerable property
body: When using a Kotlin-generated JavaScript file, I have encountered problems with `$metadata$` while I was iterating over the properties of an object. I had to add ad-hoc guards to check for the presence of `$metadata$`. For better interop with JavaScript and its libraries, I believe Kotlin should avoid or at least hide these metadata properties on JS objects. For more background: https://gist.github.com/staltz/f5ed815dc54c6433d5f8
